-- Onion Prices in India Rise as Much as 50% as Supply Shrinks, DNA Reports
-- B y   M a d e l e n e   P e a r s o n
-- 2010-11-16T01:25:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-16/onion-prices-in-india-rise-as-much-as-50-as-supply-shrinks-dna-reports.html
Onions prices have risen at least 50
percent in India, DNA newspaper reported. Onions are selling at
30 rupees to 40 rupees per kilogram, up from 15 rupees per
kilogram, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
